RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 12600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JULY 15, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR IOWA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 15, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLE ROCKER took over the lead after opening stages and set a pressured pace up the backstretch, widened to a clear advantage around the turn, hustled along two wide into the lane then shifted to the inside, had plenty left in reserve and finished going away. PAISLEY'S VISION tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, chased the leader around the turn, sustained inside bid through the lane and secured second best. LIL DITTY'S KITTY was unhurried and raced off the early pace, picked up the tempo late on the turn, swung three to four wide into the lane, sustained a steady bid and cleared the rest. CAMCORDIA tracked up close three wide, hustled along in contention around the turn then faded in the lane. YANKEE PRIDE raced off the top flight up the backstretch, chased three to four wide into the lane and never threatened. GAME TO PLAY broke on top then conceded position to the eventual winner, remained forwardly placed up the backstretch, flattened mid-way around the turn and continued to tire in the drive.

CONSTITUTION DAY sprinted out for the lead and led the way by clear margins while under a slight hold, continued well clear around the turn, began to tire in the final furlong, got overtaken in the final sixteenth and finished well clear over the rest. SKYFLYER raced off the early pace, hustled along two wide around the turn, sustained bid through the lane and captured show. SPEEDBAYOU was up close in the opening quarter then weakened and dropped to the inside, saved ground around the turn, gained position in upper stretch then flattened and lost show. BIG VANILLA stumbled at the start, hustled up and raced behind the clear leader in the opening quarter, chased three wide around the turn then came up empty. SCRUGGS was off a step slow at the start, raced near the back and retreated.

NATIVE HELLRAISER raced in the last flight, picked up the tempo mid-way around the turn, ran on four wide through the lane and just missed show. DREADPIRATEROBERTS raced off the early pace, chased on the inside around the turn, tipped two wide for the drive and lacked a needed rally. ROWDY RAY pressed the pace up the backstretch, weakened off the leader midway around the turn, sustained run just off the inside to the furlong marker then came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOLIDAY TICKET raced in the last flight through early stages, moved up closer three wide mid-way around the turn, swung four wide into the lane, quickly gathered ground, swept by and finished going away. MINE MY TIME raced off the early pace, ranged up closer and slipped through along the rail late on the turn, cut the corner, slipped through again on weakening leader approaching the furlong marker, briefly held the lead then got overtaken by the winner. ROCK CITY ROCKET raced between foes early then dropped to last, saved ground around the turn, shifted out in upper stretch and gained show. GETTINHOT'NHERE sprinted out to the early lead, set the uncontested pace and held clear around the turn, got collared by rail running rival approaching the eighth pole and gave way. RACE.FOOTNOTES: POKER PLAY took command soon after the start and led the way around the first turn, set the uncontested pace up the backstretch, widened advantage around the far turn, saved ground into the lane and drew off under steady encouragement. RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 88. Starter Allowance Purse 36429. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $30,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN OR CLAIMING. RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICAN POSSE rated off the top two flights up the backstretch, let out a notch and quickly circled up five wide mid-way around the turn, cleared command at the quarter pole, angled in a couple paths in upper stretch, pulled away and finisihed ridden out in the final sixteenth. TAP THE BRAKES raced off the top flight along the outside, moved up four deep to challenge for the lead mid-way around the turn, could not move on with the eventual winner at the quarter pole but sustained bid through the lane and finished second best. LEAPIN TY MAN tracked the top flight along the inside, tipped out a path and headed in pursuit entering the turn, lacked a clear path past the five sixteenths pole, waited briefly then swung out four to five wide entering the lane, finished with response, gained show and cleared the rest. STAR OF MINE set a pressured pace up the backstretch, dueled for the lead mid-way around the turn, got overtaken by the eventual winner, ran on to the eighth pole then came up empty. ELIOT NESS briefly held a slim lead then conceded position to STAR OF MINE and applied pace pressure, took on the whole field and dueled midway around the turn, came up empty past the quarter pole and retreated in the lane.
